        <body>       
 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Hannira&#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/>
                10 2d Adar&#44; 5649.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi>.<lb/></p>
            <p>My esteemed friend&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Altho&#39; it has been some time since<lb/> we have exchanged letters&#44; I feel today<lb/> that I would like to write you&#44; the&#44;<lb/> to us&#44; very happy tidings of the engagement<lb/> of our eldest daughter&#44; Grace&#44; and I<lb/> know that you will also be glad to<lb/> hear&#44; that her heart&#39;s choice as her<lb/> future partner in life&#44; is one engaged<lb/> in the Holy Vocation to which you also<lb/> have devoted your life and energies.<lb/></p>
            <p>My future son in law&#44; is Rabbiner<lb/> Dr Winter&#44; Rabbi of the Congregation<lb/> in Dresden.  Altho&#39; a young man of 30&#44;<lb/> he has so won the confidence and esteem<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of the congregation where he has<lb/> served for two years&#44; that they have<lb/> elected him to serve during life.<lb/></p>
            <p>You can well imagine my good<lb/> friend&#44; how thankful are the feelings<lb/> of myself and wife to our good<lb/> Heavenly Father that our Daughter<lb/> has made such a choice&#44; and we<lb/> have every cause to hope and think<lb/> that with God&#39;s Help&#44; her future will<lb/> be a happy one.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear wife and Grace&#44; join me<lb/> in best wishes to yourself and family<lb/> and I remain Your sincere friend<lb/> M. M. Allen.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> S. Morais.<lb/></p>
            
            <p>&#91;&#63;&#93; of<lb/> Mrs. M. N. Allen.<lb/></p>
            </body>
